validateBulkUploadJSON(fileContent).docstring:
Validates and parses the uploaded JSON file for bulk product upload.
It enforces that the file is a JSON array of products (max 100)
where each product must contain every mandatory field.
@param fileContent - string content of the file.
@returns ValidationResult with a valid flag, error message if any, and an array of products.

applyDefaultFields(product).docstring:
Applies default values to a product if missing optional fields.
These defaults are required by Magento and ensure consistency.
@param product - JSONProduct object to apply default values.
@returns The product with default fields populated.

usePermissions(allowedRoles).docstring:
usePermissions hook checks if the current users role is included in allowedRoles.
@param allowedRoles - An array of permitted roles.
@returns Boolean indicating if the user has permission.
